President Biden visited the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to express his gratitude and appreciation for their service. He thanked the employees for their dedication to protecting and serving the American people while upholding the nation's laws and values. The President shared a personal story about a friend who lost his son in a tragic accident and later lost another son in the 9/11 attacks. He emphasized the importance of not letting fear define the country and urged the DHS employees to continue their mission of keeping Americans safe. President Biden acknowledged the expanding threats and challenges faced by the DHS, including natural disasters, cybersecurity, and violence prevention. He assured the employees that he would provide them with the necessary resources to carry out their duties effectively. The President recognized the sacrifices made by the families of DHS employees and emphasized their important role as well. He concluded by expressing his heartfelt gratitude to the department and its personnel for their service.